    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-03-07T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-03-07T23:00:00-05:00" n="598"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d598">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">751G.00/3–854: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Hanoi</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SPJ1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sturm</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hanoi</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-03-08T12:00:00+08:00"
                            >March 8, 1954—noon</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>478. Repeated information Saigon 373, Paris 197. Paris limit distribution.
                    General <persName corresp="#p_CGR1">Cogny</persName> says evidence appears to be
                    converging toward indication that Viet Minh will attack Dien-Bien-Phu, now that
                    Viet Minh Division 308 has withdrawn from advanced positions in Laos. <persName
                        corresp="#p_CGR1">Cogny</persName> admits, however, that there may be some
                    degree of wishful thinking in his analysis, since he continues to believe that
                    such attack would be highly advantageous to his own forces.</p>
                <p>Following period of relative calm in delta last two weeks in February, Viet Minh
                    activity this area has been stepped up appreciably since beginning of March.
                        <persName corresp="#p_CGR1">Cogny</persName> referred to Viet Minh sabotage
                    of 11 planes at Gialam airport (<gloss target="#t_Contel1">Contel</gloss>
                        472)<note n="1" xml:id="d598fn1">Telegram 472 from Hanoi, Mar. 4, reporting
                        the sabotaging that day of 11 aircraft at Hanoi civil airport, is not
                        printed. (751G.5/3–454)</note> as “a bitter blow,” but expressed hope that
                    more of the damaged aircraft could be salvaged than at first appeared
                    likely.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SPJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sturm</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
